@startuml
title Attack graph: shared factors feeding composable protocols
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #EEE8D5
  BorderColor #657B83
  FontColor #073642
}
left to right direction

rectangle "Bridge\n(shared factor)" as bridge #FFD9B3
rectangle "Minting\nSigner" as signer #FFD9B3
rectangle "Oracle\n(shared factor)" as oracle #FFD9B3
rectangle "Unbacked\nCollateral" as coll

rectangle "Aave\n(~40% usage)" as aave #B3E5B3
rectangle "Morpho\n(~30% usage)" as morpho #B3E5B3
rectangle "Spark\n(~30% usage)" as spark #B3E5B3

bridge --> signer
signer --> coll
oracle --> coll
coll --> aave
coll --> morpho
coll --> spark

note bottom of signer
  First-loss coverage is allocated
  to each shared factor in proportion
  to the protocol usage that flows
  through it, not only at the endpoints.
end note
@enduml
